Some Important Release Deadlines are fast approaching.  See also the release schedule online


http://bioconductor.org/developers/release-schedule/



The last day for any NEW package to be accepted and released under Bioc 3.9 is this Wed. April 24th.  Packages accepted after this day will remain in Biocnoductor devel and included in the Bioc 3.10 release in fall.


This Friday April 26th is the last recommended day to commit changes (documentation , bug fixes, etc) to the devel branch. This is to allow all changes to propagate and build on the build system prior to branching. The branch will be frozen and branched on Monday April 29 th.  All packages should be passing building and check without ERROR and WARNINGS by Friday April 26th.  If a package is failing across all three platforms the package will be considered for deprecation depending on the length and severity of the ERRORS.


If anyone has any questions of concerns please feel free to ask here on the mailing list.

